                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 128.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Motley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Fish</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi> D. C.</placeName>, <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1870-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23, 1870</date>. (Received at 1.30 p.
                        m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington City</hi>:</p>
                <p>Lord Granville has just informed me that her Majesty’s government have urged
                    France and Prussia to agree to an armistice with the view to the constituent
                    assembly and an eventual peace.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>MOTLEY, <hi rend="italic">London.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
